<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 5:44PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL IMPACT PITTSBURG COUNTY THROUGH 615 PM
CDT...
At 543 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles north of Scipio to 3 miles northwest of
Savanna to Kiowa. Movement was east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Krebs...
Kiowa...                          Savanna...
Crowder...                        Alderson...
Canadian...                       Indianola...
Haywood...                        Mcalester Regional Airport...
Scipio...                         Blanco...
Pittsburg...                      Arpelar...
Dow...                            Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
